Date: 23rd April 1810 - Size: Small - Location: South of Lleida,
Catalonia\\Scenario Briefing: Combat of Margalef - The Spanish
general O'Donnell foolishly advanced to the relief of Lleida
with his two divisions miles apart. When Ibarrola's lead division
came in contact with the French it fell back to receive support
from the other division but was closely pursued by the enemy
and forced to make a stand at Margalef. Historically, the French
cuirassiers quickly routed the Spanish cavalry and then fell
on the flank of the infantry before it could form square. O'Donnell
arrived with Pirez's division too late to prevent disaster. However,
to give the Spanish a better fighting chance, Pirez's troops
may arrive earlier than they did historically.\\Recommended Rules:
Default - with the following alterations - Movement Threat Disorder
and Line Movement Disruption ON
